added.title: The Guy
added.description: Gumball and Darwin put Anais' new friend, Josh, through a series of tests, to see if he's good enough for their sister. However, when the boys' extreme methods start freaking Josh out, he questions whether being Anais's friend is worth the trouble. So Gumball and Darwin end up having to convince Josh to give Anais a second chance.

added.title: The Heist
added.description: Richard discovers going into a bank whilst wearing a motorcycle helmet can land you in a lot of trouble.

added.title: The Compilation
added.description: A compilation of some of the funniest, most bizarre clips uploaded onto the internet by the people of Elmore. Clips include Banana Joe's self-choreographed acrobatics, Richard's latest culinary invention and Gumball and Darwin's contest for who can pull the weirdest face.

added.title: The Countdown
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are running late for school but need to arrive in time to avoid expulsion. Gumball and Darwin hit snooze too many times on their alarm clock and miss the school-bus. Miss Simian has threatened to expel them if they don't get to school on time. A mysterious clock appears showing exactly how long they have to get to school. When it looks like they aren't going to make it in time, they stop the clock which effects the space/time continuum.

added.title: The Triangle
added.description: Gumball is jealous when Darwin discovers a hidden musical talent, and he may not be the only one. Darwin joins the school marching band, and his tin-whistle talent lands him the solo. Gumball misses having his friend to goof off with and tries to get rehearsal cancelled. So when Darwin's whistle is sabotaged nobody believes Gumball is innocent. Gumball, meanwhile, sets out to find the true culprit, or there may be no encore.

added.title: The Flower
added.description: When Gumball sees Leslie with Penny, he is overcome with uncontrollable jealousy.

added.title: The Boombox
added.description: Gumball and Darwin try to understand Juke's urgent Beatbox message, but why won't he just speak English?!!

added.title: The Refund
added.description: Gumball and Darwin unsuccessfully attempt to get a refund for their computer game.

added.title: The Secret
added.description: Gumball almost loses his mind trying to guess Darwin's secret.

added.title: 4 on 1
added.description: Onion's fear of crowds threatens his basketball team's success.

added.title: Hotdog's Movie Premiere
added.description: Apple and Onion square off against a no-nonsense security guard after they're banned from the premiere of their friend Hot Dog's new movie.

added.title: Bottle Catch
added.description: Apple and Onion's favorite game attracts some unexpected attention.

added.title: Pancake's Bus Tour
added.description: Apple and Onion go on a guided bus tour as part of their plan to get Apple's shoe back.

added.title: Block Party
added.description: Apple and Onion have to outwit a mean duck who's taken over their building's roof.

added.title: Reeking Havoc/Live & Let Dynamo
added.description: Reeking Havoc: This year, the Professor's submission for the 2nd Annual Townsville Chili Cookoff is X-tra special. But this X-tra special ingredient doesn't settle well with Townsville's tummies./Live and Let Dynamo: Dynamo is terrorizing Townsville but who's working the controls? Now, the girls have to battle their own robot while trying to discover who is trying to pit their own weapon against them.

added.title: Film Flam
added.description: A sleazy director arrives in Townsville to make a film about the Powerpuff Girls. But this Hollywood type wants more out of Townsville than an Oscar-winning film.

added.title: Monkey See, Doggie Do/Mommy Fearest
added.description: Monkey See, Doggie Do: Mojo unleashes a curse on Townsville that turns everyone into dogs, including the Powerpuff Girls! Luckily, they manage to sniff out a solution and show Mojo that their bite is worse than his bark./Mommy Fearest: When Professor Utonium falls for the lovely Ima Goodlady, the girls quickly discover that Ima's not such a good lady after all. She's really the sinister Sedusa!

added.title: Get Back Jojo
added.description: Mojo goes back in time to try and stop the Professor from having the inspiration for the perfect little girls. Little does he know that in doing so he provides just the spark the young Professor needs.

added.title: Collect Her/Supper Villain
added.description: Collect Her: A fan of the Powerpuff Girls has collected every bit of Powerpuff stuff available, almost. His collection will be complete with three more items./Supper Villain: The girls' neighbor reveals he's not exactly the nice guy next door. But how will they capture him during a seemingly innocent dinner party?

added.title: Monstra-City/Shut the Pup Up
added.description: Monstra-city: When all the monsters move from Monster Isle to Townsville, it's up to the Girls to keep the peace./Shut the Pup Up: When the Talking Dog witnesses a crime, he moves in with the girls for protection. But the girls soon realize this chatterbox dog is less than the perfect pet.

added.title: Toast of the Town/Divide and Conquer
added.description: Toast of the Town: When the Mayor rubs Chemical X on his head for hair growth, all of him grows and stomps through Townsville./Divide and Conquer: When the Amoeba Boys learn how to divide, they multiply wreaking havoc as the many amoebas descend upon Townsville.

added.title: Speed Demon/Mojo Jonesin'
added.description: Mojo Jonesin':  When the children of Pokey Oaks become envious of the girls' superpowers, a mysterious figure offers them Chemical X. Now, the girls must fight their own classmates who have powers equal to their own./Speed Demon: The girls accidentally fly at the speed of light and when they arrive home, everything has changed. Fifty years have passed and the world has been taken over by Him.

added.title: The Trouble with Truth
added.description: The JLA find themselves in danger of losing Wonder Woman when the goddess Athena comes to Earth with an offer Diana can't refuse, filling the position of the Goddess of Truth on Mt. Olympus.

added.title: Get a Clue
added.description: Strongarm flexes her detective muscles to solve a baffling series of Decepticon thefts. Can she stand up to her teammates, in order to bring a perp to justice?

added.title: Disordered Personalities
added.description: An experiment in combining accidentally causes the Autobots to swap personalities. Stuck in the wrong bodies, the team is called on a mission to defeat the Stunticons in a road race.

added.title: The Golden Knight
added.description: An ancient Cybertronian signal sends Bumblebee and chivalry-obsessed Fixit to a remote English island for a routine scouting mission that quickly turns into the duo's very own call to adventure!

added.title: Railroad Rage
added.description: The Bee Team races to keep the Stunticons from stealing a runaway train's fusion engine, and then prevent it from crashing into the Crown City Train Station.

added.title: Moon Breaker
added.description: Optimus Prime arrives to recruit Drift for a special mission, sparking a competition between Sideswipe and Strongarm over who'd be better suited to take Drift's spot. All this while the Autobots venture to the moon to recover a dangerous weapon before Motormaster and his spacefaring Stunticons can get to it.

added.title: Breathing Room
added.description: The tight confines of the caverns has everyone on edge, so Bee goes on a scouting mission, only to be captured by Steeljaw's Decepticons who also manage to capture the squabbling Sideswipe and Strongarm. Fixit, along for the mission, does his best to keep Steeljaw and the 'Cons at bay in the depths of the subway chamber junction while all the captured Autobots work to free themselves and defeat the 'Cons.

added.title: Something He Ate
added.description: When Underbite eats part of the Autobots' GroundBridge, the Bee Team have to chase the teleporting 'Con through the desert, the forest, and even outer space!

added.title: Five Fugitives
added.description: The Autobots' pursuit of Steeljaw hits an unexpected roadblock when Strongarm's old mentor DETECTIVE DROPFORGE arrives from Cybertron with orders to arrest the Bee Team!

added.title: Freedom Fighters
added.description: As the Bee Team struggles to liberate Cybertron from the Decepticon‑ controlled High Council, Optimus and his All Stars fight back the advance force of an Earth‑bound Cybertronian invasion!

removed.title: Exiles
removed.description: Steeljaw and his pack return and launch an attack on the Scrapyard, forcing the Autobots to abandon their home base. As a result, Sideswipe's fear of abandonment threatens the Bee Team when they face their foes again at the Crown River Dam.

removed.title: Sick as a Bot
removed.description: After the Energon seeking WINGCODE infects the Autobots with a virus, Bulkhead joins Grimlock in his frantic hunt for the Decepticon. But to capture the 'Con, the duo of brawny Bots has to learn to keep their cool and come up with a workable plan.

removed.title: The Fastest Bot Alive!
removed.description: Grimlock acquires uncontrollable superspeed, which proves to be a problem when the Autobots have to deal with a revenge‑minded Simacore and his army of Mini‑Con clones.

removed.title: Prepare for Departure
removed.description: The Bee Team struggles to recover a canister with radioactive fuel rods from Steeljaw and his pack, while Grimlock struggles to learn the difference between work and play.

removed.title: Collateral Damage
removed.description: Soundwave finally escapes the Shadow Zone to set up a Beacon Generator intended to summon Megatron! While the Bee Team engages the notorious Decepticon atop a skyscraper, Optimus Prime takes on Laserbeak in the skies over Crown City, and Sideswipe learns a lesson in considering the consequences of his actions.

removed.title: Out of the Shadows
removed.description: The Bee Team learns about Drift's past when his former mentor Shadow Raker comes to Earth to recover something Drift has taken from him‑ Slipstream and Jetstorm!

removed.title: Guilty as Charged
removed.description: Strongarm worries that her Academy classmate Chicane may still harbor a grudge, but when a powerful foe comes after her old friend, Strongarm and the Bee Team put their sparks on the line to protect her.

removed.title: The Great Divide
removed.description: After once again accidentally combining into the Ultra Bee Team Combiner, the Autobots find Sideswipe has split into two individuals -­ each being one extreme of his personality. Now, the two Sideswipes must overcome their differences and learn to work together as the Bee Team pursues Stunticon Drag Strip, who stole a dangerous Cybertronian device - the Gravitic Adjuster.

removed.title: Defrosted
removed.description: Grimlock begs to learn new fighting methods from reluctant "teacher" Drift and puts them into action when The Autobots travel to the Antarctic to battle the Decepticon Prong - unfrozen from a melting glacier. Grim must put Drift's lessons to use in order to defeat the Decepticon and save the research team stuck there.

removed.title: Combine and Conquer
removed.description: Feeling the Autobots need to step up their game, Bee insists they follow his orders to the letter. But this new leadership style is put to the test when Motormaster and the Stunticons go after a Meteorite Deflector Dish‑ and the Bee Team is forced to combine and improvise together to take on Menasor!

removed.title: Sphere of Influence
removed.description: The Bee Team discovers a mysterious artifact that has a strange effect on Cybertronian minds, turning the bots against one another! Can the Bee Team get it together in time to keep obsessed treasure-­hunter Springload from accidentally destroying Crown City?

removed.title: People Pleaser
removed.description: Blossom neglects her promise to Bubbles when she takes on too many things leaving Buttercup and Bubbles to fend for themselves.

removed.title: The Powerpuff Girls: A Documentary/Girls Gone Mild
removed.description: The Powerpuff Girls a Documentary: A film student attempts to do a documentary on the Powerpuff Girls and learns catching these superheroes at rest is harder than he thought./Girls Gone Mild: When Parents Against Powerpuffs tell the girls that their superheroics are becoming too imitable, the girls must hold back on fighting crime.

removed.title: Fashion Forward
removed.description: When the Fashionistas launch a new line of brainwashing clothing, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop the fashion trend before it's too late.

removed.title: Candy Is Dandy/Catastrophe
removed.description: Candy Is Dandy: When the Mayor gives the girls some candy in gratitude for saving the day, they become hooked on the stuff. They even make a deal with a local villain to commit crimes for treats./Catastrophe: A monster is frantically tearing up the town looking for his lost kitty. But in a city the size of Townsville, how can the girls find one lone cat?

removed.title: A Made Up Story
removed.description: Someone is defacing all the posters and statues of Townsville with make-up. Can the girls stop this makeover takeover or will they get the blush off?

removed.title: Snow Month
removed.description: After a snow day saves Blossom from having to face a boy who's asked her out, she decides to use her ice breath to keep it going even if that means plunging Townsville into eternal winter complete with monstrous yetis!

removed.title: Mo' Linguish/Oops I Did It Again
removed.description: Mo' Linguish: Mojo is sentenced to do community service for Townsville and begins teaching English at the Learning Annex. Soon everyone is speaking in circles like Mojo and the town comes to a standstill./Oops I Did It Again: When the Professor realizes that all his successful experiments are actually just accidents, he sets out to do something brilliant on purpose!

removed.title: Deb O'Nair
removed.description: A classy queen of etiquette makes the Utoniums question their superhero way of life.

removed.title: The Tell Tale Schedulebot
removed.description: After Blossom and Buttercup break Schedulebot, they'll do anything to keep the truth from coming out.

removed.title: Beat Your Greens/Down 'N Dirty
removed.description: Beat Your Greens: When Broccoli Aliens from space invade Townsville, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls and all the children of Townsville to take a bite out of crime. Down N' Dirty: When Buttercup refuses to take a bath, the town kicks her out. But Buttercup decides to stick with her stink until her favorite thing is taken away from her.

removed.title: Twisted Sister/Cover Up
removed.description: Twisted Sister: The girls decide they need some help fighting crime so they create another Powerpuff Girl. But they don't get the combination of sugar, spice and everything nice quite right./Cover Up: Blossom and Bubbles learn that Buttercup has secretly been rubbing a security blanket before every battle to make herself a super fighter. Can the girls convince Buttercup that her strength is within?

removed.title: Something's a Ms./Slumbering with the Enemy
removed.description: Something's a Ms: Miss Bellum is acting very strange lately. And she keeps showing up at crime scenes. Has our favorite secretary gone to the dark side, or is there another woman involved here?/Slumbering With The Enemy: When the girls decide to have an all-girl slumber party, a villain decides to crash it. To what lengths will this villain go to keep his identity hidden?

removed.title: Mini Golf Madness
removed.description: Buttercup takes her game winning mini golf ball, in spite of ominous warnings of dire consequences.

removed.title: The Buttercup Job
removed.description: Buttercup joins Jemmica in a quest for adventure, but how far will she go?

removed.title: Roughing It Up/What's the Big Idea
removed.description: Roughing It Up: The girls and the Professor set out on an old-fashioned vacation to the Townsville Swamp. Trouble is, Fuzzy and his nephews are there, too./What's the Big Idea: 20 story high Powerpuff Girls spell disaster for Townsville when they delicately try to stop Mojo from taking over.

removed.title: Custody Battle/City of Nutsville
removed.description: Custody Battle: Mojo discovers the Rowdyruff Boys are back and is determined to show them that he is a more evil dad than Him./The City of Nutsville: The squirrels of Townsville are chirping mad! But when Bubbles loses her ability to speak a squirrel, the girls don't know how to calm the rodents down.

removed.title: 'Twas the Fight Before Christmas
removed.description: When Princess Morbucks tries to ruin Christmas for the children of the world, the Powerpuff Girls must save the day.

removed.title: Poorbucks
removed.description: When Morbucks loses her money, Blossom tries to reform her.

removed.title: Take Your Kids to Dooms Day
removed.description: The Girls spend the day with the Professor at his boring office, only to find that the office comes with a terrible secret.

removed.title: The Secret Life of Blossom Powerpuff
removed.description: When Blossom can't join her favorite school club, she imagines what her life would be like if she joined other clubs.

removed.title: Tiara Trouble
removed.description: Bubbles' excitement over being a contestant in the Townsville Beauty, Talent and All-Around Flair pageant is ruined when Blossom and Buttercup become overbearing stage-sisters. But when a mysterious tiara causes trouble for the contestants, they realize there are bigger problems at hand.

removed.title: You're a Good Man, Mojo Jojo
removed.description: The holidays are Mojo's favorite time…for ruining everything! But this year, he may just learn the reason for the season.

removed.title: Imaginary Fiend/Cootie Gras
removed.description: Imaginary Fiend: The new boy in school has a special friend nobody else can see. When this imaginary friend begins destroying the class, the girls must imagine how to stop him./Cootie Gras: Mojo observes that everyone is staying away from little Harry Pitt because he has cooties. So Mojo concocts a plan to keep the girls away by using this cootie-covered boy as bait.

removed.title: Best Day Ever
removed.description: Joker frees Luthor with a mother box and forces him to spend the day together, hopping all over the world, with the Justice League hot on their trail trying to catch up.

removed.title: The Brain Buster
removed.description: A mysterious creature abducts Batman, Mr. Terrific, Luthor and two of the brainiest villains in the universe to put them to the test to discover who is the smartest among them.

removed.title: Watchtower Tours
removed.description: When Booster Gold starts to secretly give tours of the Watchtower to make some extra cash, he inadvertently brings in a super villain disguised as a tourist.

removed.title: She Wore Red Velvet
removed.description: When Booster and the JLA come under attack by a mysterious and unrelenting new villainess known as Red Velvet, Booster comes to realize she's actually the fiance he left at the altar in the future.

removed.title: Party Animal
removed.description: Green Arrow, who is determined to finally throw a successful holiday party for the Justice League, finds his plans thwarted when Plastic Man brings a tranquilized super villain to the gathering.

removed.title: Harley Goes Ape!
removed.description: When Gorilla Grodd takes control over Titano, the giant ape, the only person who seems to be able to override his control is the medical worker who nursed him as a chimp. She's now known as Harley Quinn.

removed.title: Bored to Be Wild
removed.description: Mega Man teams up with his crush, Ashley Adderley, to solve a series of science riddles left by Chemical Man, who's plotting to turn all the city's metal into rubber.

removed.title: Enter the Wood Man
removed.description: Mega Man accidentally awakens Wood Man, who thinks it's still the Hard Age, sets off on a path of destruction toward Silicon City.

removed.title: The GI
removed.description: Gumball and Darwin's martial arts costumes make them a laughing stock at school.

removed.title: The Money
removed.description: The Wattersons have run out of money and are torn between being broke and selling out. Richard has lost all of the family's money. Nicole is happy for the Wattersons to appear in a Joyful Burger commercial for some much needed cash. However Gumball protests as he is convinced it's selling out. He persuades the family to stick to their principles, but they find sticking to a tiny budget even harder.

removed.title: The Sweaters
removed.description: Gumball and Darwin's reputation is challenged and they really couldn't care less...

removed.title: The Console
removed.description: When Gumball is given a cursed videogame console, Elmore becomes trapped inside a fantasy RPG world. Gumball, Darwin and Anais have to battle their way through town, unraveling the secrets of their new virtual reality. But they'll have to level up if they're going to stand any chance against the mysterious final boss.

removed.title: The Uploads
removed.description: Gumball and Darwin try to tear themselves away from the internet, but end up falling down the Elmore Stream-hole.

removed.title: The Others
removed.description: When Anais reveals that she's in the grade above them at school, Gumball and Darwin's eyes are suddenly opened to a whole new world of other students at Elmore Junior High. Gumball is horrified to learn that there are a bunch of characters who are barely aware of his existence and is determined to force his way into their lives.

removed.title: The Mystery
removed.description: Gumball sets out to solve the mystery of who stuffed Principal Brown into his locker.

removed.title: The Amazing World of Gumball: Holiday Special
removed.description: Santa Claus gets run over by the Wattersons, so it's up to them to save Christmas.

removed.title: Christmas
removed.description: Santa Claus is coming to town. Unfortunately he gets run over by the Wattersons, so it's up to them to save Christmas.

removed.title: The Stars
removed.description: When Dad gives Larry's hairdresser a bad review for saying he's bald, he gets offered a free haircut. This inspires Gumball and Darwin to go on a reviewing spree across town, forcing Larry to give them stuff with the threat of a bad review. Just because the customer is always right doesn't mean that what they're doing isn't wrong.

removed.title: The Best
removed.description: No matter what Gumball does, Carmen thinks she knows better. Gumball attempts to gain the moral high ground but fails spectacularly.  He decides that self-improvement isn't his style. The only option he has left is to bring Carmen down to his level.

removed.title: The Lie
removed.description: Gumball and Anais invent a new holiday to beat the January blues. The citizens of Elmore are feeling down because it's January, so Gumball and Anais invent a new holiday called Sluzzle Tag. The whole town embrace this festival and get excited about the arrival of the Sluzzle Dude; leaving it to Gumball and Anais to keep everyone's Sluzzle Tag dreams alive.

removed.title: The Hatching
removed.description: The Ninja learn more about the Krux and Acronix, the two fallen Elemental Masters known as the Hands of Time, and are sure this threat has finally been eliminated. But with Wu out of action and suffering from the effects of the Time Punch, the Ninja discover a new enemy in their midst, the Vermillion Warriors. And the Ninjas have no idea who controls them.
